 The accident took place at around 12:00 between the Woestalleen and Arnot offramps. The driver of the bakkie had veered onto the grass embankment next to the highway and the vehicle overturned. Nobody else was involved in the accident and the driver was rushed to hospital with serious injuries.      One dead in early morning crash Fake notes in Belfast leads to two arrests Theft of motor vehicles on the rise Accident claims the life of an infant • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za